%p
  I have been working on BipolarType since the early 1980s when I was diagnosed as
  =link_to 'bipolar', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bipolar_disorder', class: 'external'
  at around the same time I learned about
  =succeed '.' do
    =link_to 'personality type', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Personality_type', class: 'external'
%p
  The
  =link_to 'theory', theory_path
  is scientific (it is
  =succeed ')' do
    =link_to 'falsifiable', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falsifiability', class: 'external'
  but it has not been validated by the medical, psychiatric, psychological, or type communities.
%p
  I am sharing it on the web because it helps
  =(link_to 'me', my_path).period
  I hope that you will find it useful or interesting but I do not guarantee it to be either true or helpful.
%p
  After you identify
  =link_to 'your', answer_path(Answer.first_path)
  BipolarType, you can
  =(link_to 'change the words', words_path)
  for the sixteen actions: use words with positive connotations for your eight
  ="do".dquote.pluralize
  and negative connotations for your eight
  ="do not".dquote.pluralize
